Name: NITROGLYCERIN
Melting Point: Crystalizes in 2 forms: labile form, 2.8 °C; stable form, 13.5 °C

Name: Cobaltous citrate
Melting Point: Rose-red, amorphous powder; melting point 150 °C (loses 2H2O); slightly soluble in water; soluble in dilute acids /Cobalt(II) citrate dihydrate/

Name: COPPER(II) HYDROXIDE
Melting Point: Decomposes at melting point, with loss of water.

Name: BERYLLIUM PHOSPHATE
Melting Point: White solid. MP: 100 °C (loses water)  (decomposes). Soluble in water, acetic acid. /Beryllium phosphate trihydrate/

Name: BERYLLIUM FLUORIDE
Melting Point: True MP: 555 °C; becomes free-flowing at about 800 °C

Name: DISODIUM HYDROGEN PHOSPHATE
Melting Point: MP: loses H2O at 92.5 °C; Specific gravity: 2.066 at 15 °C /Disodium phosphate dihydrate/

Name: FERRIC NITRATE
Melting Point: MP: 47 °C. Freely soluble in water, alcohol, acetone; slightly soluble in cold concentrated nitric acid. /Ferric nitrate nonahydrate/

Name: FERROUS CITRATE
Melting Point: White microscopic rhombic, orthorhombic crystals; mp: decomposition at 350 °C in molecular hydrogen; soluble in ammonium hydroxide. /Monohydrate/

Name: FERROUS GLUCONATE
Melting Point: The melting point for D-gluconic acid, ferrous salt dihydrate (98%) is 188 °C, decomposes. The specific optical rotation is +6.7 deg at 25 °C (c=1, H2O). /Dihydrate/

Name: AMMONIUM SILICOFLUORIDE
Melting Point: TWO MODIFICATIONS @ ROOM TEMP: STABLE, CUBIC PHASE; METASTABLE, TRIGONAL PHASE

Name: METHENAMINE
Melting Point: Sublimes at about 260 °C without melting and with partial decomposition

Name: ALUMINUM NITRATE
Melting Point: Melting point 73.5 °C. Decomposition to nitric acid and basic aluminum nitrates ... begins at 130 °C. Dissociation to aluminum oxide and oxides of nitrogen occurs above 500 °C.  /Nonahydrate/

Name: ISODECYL ALCOHOL
Melting Point: FP: LESS THAN 140 °F= LESS THAN 60 °C= LESS  THAN 333 DEG K

Name: LINALOOL
Melting Point: Freezing point: below -74 °C /OECD Guideline 102 (Melting point / Melting Range)/

Name: LITHIUM AMIDE
Melting Point: Starts to decompose at 320 °C and melts at 375 °C

Name: SODIUM ALUMINUM HYDRIDE
Melting Point: Begins to melt at 183 °C with decomposition to evolve hydrogen

Name: CARVONE
Melting Point: MP: 25.2 °C. Very soluble in ethanol; soluble in ether, carbon tetrachloride, chloroform /L-Carvone/

Name: SODIUM METHOXIDE
Melting Point: Melting point: decomp. Soluble in cold water. Soluble in methanol. /Solvated form/

Name: SODIUM SILICOFLUORIDE
Melting Point: Melts at red heat with decomposition.

Name: TEFLON
Melting Point: Melts to an extremely viscous gel at 327 °C

Name: TETRAHYDROPHTHALIC ANHYDRIDE
Melting Point: Crystals from petroleum ether. MP: 103.5 °C. Soluble in ethanol, acetone, chloroform, benzene; slightly soluble in petroleum ether. /cis-1,2,3,6-Tetrahydrophthalic anhydride/

Name: THORIUM NITRATE
Melting Point: White, crystalline mass. MP: 500 °C (decomposes). Soluble in water and alcohol. /Tetrahydrate/

Name: Chloroacetic acid
Melting Point: Exists in alpha, beta, and gamma forms having mp 63 °C, 55-56 °C, and 50 °C respectively. MP for acid of commerce: 61-63 °C

Name: CHROMIUM(III) ACETATE
Melting Point: >400 °C (OECD Guideline 102 (Melting point / Melting Range) resp. EU A.1 (melting / freezing temperature))

Name: URANIUM OXYSULFATE
Melting Point: MP: decomposes at 100 °C; sol: 24.3 g/100 cc concn sulfuric acid at 13 °C; sol: 30 g/100 cc concn hydrochloric acid at 13 °C 20.5 g/100 cc water at 15.5 °C, 22.2 g/100 cc water at 100 °C /Trihydrate/

Name: NONYLPHENOL
Melting Point: Freezing point: -10 °C (sets to glass below this temperature)

Name: POLYCHLOROPRENE
Melting Point: Varies with the temperature of crystallization, and the time and temperature of any subsequent annealing; approximately 30-70 °C

Name: METHYL CHLOROFORMATE
Melting Point: Less than -114 °F= less than -81 °C= less than 192 deg K

Name: POLYVINYL CHLORIDE
Melting Point: NOTCHED IZOD IMPACT STRENGTH: 0.4-2.0 FT LB/IN; ROCKWELL HARDNESS: R110-R120; HEAT DISTORTION 264 LB/SQ IN: 60-80 °C; SPECIFIC HEAT: 0.2-0.28 CAL/G; LINEAR THERMAL EXPANSION COEFFICIENT, 1X10-5; 5.0-18 °C; MAX CONTINUOUS SERVICE TEMP: 70-74 °C; /UNMODIFIED, RIGID PVC/

Name: POTASSIUM BROMATE
Melting Point: 350 °C; decomposes at 370 °C with evolution of oxygen.
